You'd be surprised how many people don't grasp this concept.  I can remember times in places like skyplane, Veeshan's Peak, Temple of Veeshan, Kael/Skyshrine, all the way down to the Elemental Planes and now PoTime, where we complained about one part of the zone or another - helping them tune it as to loot or mob difficulty or whatever.  These 'rants' were usually public, and inevitably every time someone would pipe up with 'who cares, its only affecting the top 0.1%!' or 'you only care about YOU'.  <br>
<br>
How many have raided in those zones?  Do you like them now?  Do you like the loot progression from say, VP to ToV?  When we first got to ToV for instance, the drakes had an AE dispell and hit extremely harder than what they do now.  Because of efforts of FoH and other guilds on the same level, these zones are made playable.  Everyone who comes afterward benefits.  Don't say you'll never be there either - I remember the same being said for ToVN.  It all just takes time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tsurok@graffeswizardcompilation>Tsurok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/03 9:31 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: emm</span><hr size=1> /agree Vorkreider.  At least, my eye of zomm can open the door, but its got to be right next to it in order to do so, for some reason.  However, that doesn't make things any better, really<br>
<br>
I don't mind that I couldn't reasonably get the spell at 39, but at 53, it should be easier than it is.  The COM skel is inconsistent with the difficulty of the other two skels because 1) it requires charm, 2) it lies beyond a locked door requiring raid level force (if you do it without exploiting by warping the skel down or using zone geography), and 3) Has ph's meaning its not always up.<br>
<br>
Concussion should be easily accessible to a lvl 51 wizard.  Why?  Well, lets look at the other DPS classes and compare aggro reducing abilities while grouped...<br>
<br>
1.  Rogue - evade ability at lvl 10?  Can't remember when this started on mine, but it was real early.<br>
2.  Monk - FD ability at lvl 17<br>
3.  Ranger - Jolt - vendor purchased spell at lvl 51.<br>
4.  Wizard - concussion - quested lvl 39 spell<br>
5.  Necro - FD spell - lvl 16, but I doubt they use it much in this capacity.<br>
<br>
This leaves only mages out of aggro reducing spell, but they can cast judiciously and still do more dps than a like level wizard because of their pet, not to mention focus items.  At least, at my level they can.  <br>
<br>
Given this, I think concussion balances the wizard class with the other dps classes in groups.  I don't mind questing for it, but the current COM skel is out of whack with the rest of the quest.<br>
<br>
-Tsu<br>
53.8 channeler  <br>
<br>
