Given the comments by GZ I suspect the quest was thought to be properly challenging for a group around level 39 by the quest designers.  There's been ample evidence in the past that not everyone working on this game is aware of what's feasible, logical and balanced.  Every other quest from Kunark is possible, if boring and long, to do at the appropriate level.  This one is very, very difficult to even attempt at this level (particularly if you don't have pre-printed maps and a heavily camped Karnor's Castle).  The quest guys screwed up, but won't fix it.  Since the stupid kludge to get around this error has been removed, it's time to fix the quest.  Even if its not related to what they call an &quot;exploit&quot; at uber level encounters.<br>
<br>
It's a sad but true fact: if you want something fixed in this game that's being ignored, the 100% best way to do so is find a way for very high level characters in uber areas to gain an advantage by using the flaw.  That's how Eye of Zomm was fixed, for example.  Hurts the characters?  Well, we'll get around to it some day.  Helps the characters?  SHUT DOWN THE GAME!!!! STAT!!!! PATCH IT!! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bayler>Bayler</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/03 11:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: emm</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>There's been ample evidence in the past that not everyone working on this game is aware of what's feasible, logical and balanced. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
